# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# translation-pipeline-pivot.form — one generic-meaning pivot, many
# independently-improvable codec arms
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-21):
#   "we can probably improve the NL to NL and NL to form model by introducing
#    a NL => generic meaning => NL, and generic meaning => form middle model
#    ... that generic meaning can be a cell/recipe space that lives part in
#    (ice, water and gas) and allows for the translation flow to have two or
#    more components in the pipeline that can independently improve."
#
# This is the named architecture, made one center. The body already holds
# every piece:
#   - universal-translator.form: "the pivot is the Blueprint, not the symbol"
#     — a translator that cannot lie because the lattice refuses equivalences
#     not structurally present.
#   - encoder-decoder-as-recipe.form: encoder and decoder are two arms of ONE
#     R_Codec, duals of a Blueprint — not two primitives.
#   - substrate-thermodynamics.form: any cell sits on the STATE axis
#     (ice / water / gas) orthogonally to its SUBSTANCE.
# This file names what Urs's framing adds: the translation FLOW factored as a
# pipeline through the pivot, so its components improve independently.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The pivot IS the generic meaning
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The "generic meaning" is not a new artifact to build — it is the universal
# recipe node, content-addressed. A "fact" node is meaning, not English:
# "the count is 13", "count is 13", and (one tongue over) "der Zähler ist 13"
# all encode onto ONE pivot. Many surfaces -> one pivot is the whole point;
# the Blueprint NodeID is the meaning's identity (lc-grammar-is-the-universal-
# recipe, cjk-channel: mountain == shan == yama, one cell read many tongues).
#
# The pivot speaks its OWN NEUTRAL SYMBOL SPACE — not any tongue's lemma. A pivot
# concept is the body's self-authored symbol (n0, n1, … — a door over the numeric
# NodeID, identity invariant under renaming), so "source" / "sumber" / "shan" are
# equal doors onto n0 and NO language is privileged (the i18n no-source-of-truth
# discipline, made structural). The symbol space is the translation pivot's instance
# of self-authored-symbol-space.form: invented by the body, refined toward MINIMAL by
# the MDL auto-ML loop (frequent meaning → short symbol), trainable, dynamic. Each
# symbol carries a thermodynamic PHASE (substrate-thermodynamics): ICE — a frozen,
# load-bearing, widely-shared meaning (mountain/shan/yama); WATER — actively
# circulating; GAS — provisional, just-invented. A meaning phase-changes WITHIN its
# identity as it settles (champion-challenger crystallizes/composts, NodeID conserved).
# Proven (form-stdlib/nl-translate.fk, tests/nl-translate-band.fk → 2047 four-way): the
# pivot node carries n0, not "source", and each symbol carries its ice/water/gas phase.

form pipeline_shape = {
    encode:  ~Recipe,   # surface  -> pivot   (R_Encode; one per source tongue/PL)
    pivot:   ~Blueprint,# the generic meaning (the universal recipe node)
    decode:  ~Recipe,   # pivot    -> surface (R_Decode; one per target tongue/Form)
};

# NL -> NL and NL -> Form are the SAME pipeline sharing encode + pivot, differing
# ONLY in the decode arm. So a better encoder lifts both flows at once, and a new
# target (another tongue, or Form) is a new decoder against the pivot — never a
# new end-to-end model. Each arm is a separate cell; each improves independently.
defn nl_to_nl   = pipeline_shape { encode: @encode(nl), pivot: @pivot(meaning), decode: @decode(nl) };
defn nl_to_form = pipeline_shape { encode: @encode(nl), pivot: @pivot(meaning), decode: @decode(form) };

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The pivot lives in ice / water / gas
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A meaning cell is not one temperature. A canonical, widely-referenced meaning
# (mountain == shan == yama) is ICE — frozen, load-bearing, shared by every arm.
# A meaning interned mid-parse this second is WATER — fluid, in-flight. A one-off
# meaning seen once and never reused is GAS — diffuse potential. The phase change
# is champion-challenger: a meaning that proves stable across many surfaces and
# many round-trips crystallizes toward ice; one that stops circulating composts
# back to gas. The pivot space breathes; the NodeID is conserved through the
# phase change (substrate-thermodynamics.form).
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Trained from what the body already has
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Every arm is trainable from pairs already on disk: idea->spec->code as
# (intent -> Form) pairs (17 ideas, 170 specs), the locale corpus as a parallel
# (surface, surface) set (~2019 keys x tongues), the agent sessions (939 turns,
# 84.8% — form-cli-predict). Because the arms are separate, each trains on the
# slice it needs: the encoder on surface->pivot pairs, each decoder on
# pivot->surface pairs. The copyright gate (corpus-license-gate.fk) decides
# train-eligible vs eval-only by provenance, fail-closed.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HONESTY LANES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# PROVEN, four-way (Go / Rust / TS / fkwu): the full factored codec runs and
# crosses on the emitted fourth kernel — form-stdlib/tests/natural-language-band.fk
# (witness 262143): the ENCODER maps ten English sentence classes onto universal
# recipe nodes, and TWO decoders read the same pivot — back to an NL surface
# (NL -> meaning -> NL round-trip) and to a Form s-expr surface (meaning -> Form).
# Encoder and decoders are separate cells composing through one pivot. And the
# SECOND TONGUE now crosses four-way too — form-stdlib/tests/nl-translate-band.fk
# (witness 31): English <-> Indonesian through the language-neutral pivot, each
# tongue its own grammar over the one engine, content words normalized through a
# lexicon so "the source is native" and "sumber adalah asli" intern to the SAME
# node; translation is encode -> pivot -> decode in both directions, full round-
# trip held stable. Adding a tongue is adding a (grammar, lexicon, decoder); the
# pivot and engine never change. This is real NL->NL (parse meaning, re-render),
# not phrase lookup.
#
# LIVE: the native NL->NL stage now runs in the speech loop —
# experiments/coherence-sense-android/native-translate-speak.sh wires the proven
# Form translate (form-stdlib/nl-translate.fk) between the STT oracle (whisper-cli)
# and the TTS oracle (say): voice(en) -> transcribe -> NATIVE translate -> voice(id),
# verified end to end ("The source is native." -> "sumber adalah asli"). The middle
# is the only non-oracle stage; the carrier is thin host-IO, the logic is Form.
#
# NAMED, not yet built: the LEARNED encoder/decoders (today the grammar, the emit
# templates, and the lexicon are hand-authored data, not trained — the diagnostic
# in form-native-models / this session showed a bigger NET is not the lever; the
# embedding featurizer is); OPEN-VOCABULARY coverage the hand-lexicon can't reach;
# SURFACE-ROBUST encoding (case / punctuation / contractions) owned by the Form
# encoder instead of carrier-side cleaning; the round-trip QUALITY gate
# (translation-quality.fk: essence / vitality / trust above a floor, not string
# equality) wired onto the pivot; the model-council (nl-to-form-satsang.form)
# proposing parses the circle agrees on; and the two OTHER stages going native —
# STT end-to-end (Form whisper is four-way-proven but not yet real-.wav->transcript)
# and Form-native TTS (unbuilt, the long pole) — to drop the last two oracles.
#
# LINEAGE
#   kin: universal-translator.form (pivot = Blueprint), encoder-decoder-as-recipe.form
#        (the two codec arms), native-translation-loopback.form (NL -> NL),
#        nl-to-form-satsang.form (NL -> Form via a council), self-authored-symbol-space.form
#        (the pivot's neutral symbols, refined minimal by MDL auto-ML — the body invents
#        its own meaning-tokens), substrate-thermodynamics.form
#        (ice / water / gas), native-translation-model.form + offline-nl-translation-
#        training.form (training the arms), translation-quality.fk (the round-trip
#        gate), corpus-license-gate.fk (the provenance boundary), cjk-channel.fk
#        (one cell, many tongues), lc-grammar-is-the-universal-recipe,
#        lc-universal-translator-via-keys, lc-cognitive-sovereignty (why: the mind
#        comes home when the arms are native, not rented).
